From cc2589887d0f8665085ad540ab59679d4919a46b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 15:10:55 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] macOS 10.6 SDK and GCC 14 compatibility fixes for Cocoa
 GUI

Core:
- ValueUtil.h: Rename 'id' member to 'id_' to avoid ObjC keyword conflict

CtrlCore/CocoMM.h:
- Add SDK compatibility defines for modern constant names
  (NSEventModifierFlags, NSControlStateValue, NSBezelStyle, etc.)
- Add NSColorToCGColor() helper for pre-10.8 compatibility
- Undef Carbon macros (check, verify, require) that conflict with U++

CtrlCore/CocoApp.mm:
- Convert for-in loops to traditional C-style loops
- Convert property dot syntax to message syntax for NSEvent
- Conditionally compile Apple blocks (^) for Clang only
- Add runtime check for backingScaleFactor (10.7+ only)
- Use NSRectToCGRect for type conversion on 10.6

CtrlCore/CocoClip.mm:
- Replace lambda with ObjC method for GCC compatibility

CtrlCore/CocoProc.mm:
- Convert for-in loops to traditional loops
- Replace FindMatch lambda with inline loop

CtrlLib/ChCocoMM.mm:
- Remove lambdas that cause GCC 14 ObjC++ ICE
- Replace .CGColor property with NSColorToCGColor() helper
- Convert property dot syntax to message syntax
- Add respondsToSelector: checks for 10.7+ APIs
- Remove @available() which is unsupported by GCC

Draw/FontCoco.mm:
- Add kCTFontOrientationHorizontal compatibility define for 10.6

ide/Builders/Cocoa.cpp:
- Use MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET for Info.plist minimum version
  instead of hardcoded 10.13

These changes enable building Ultimate++ with GCC 14 on macOS 10.6
Snow Leopard, including PowerPC architecture support.
